problem:
According to the table below, how many dollars are in the median value of the 59 salaries paid to this company's employees?

\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|}
\hline
\textbf{Position Title}&\textbf{\# with Title}&\textbf{Salary}\\\hline
President&1&$\$130{,}000$\\\hline
Vice-President&5&$\$90{,}000$\\\hline
Director&10&$\$75{,}000$\\\hline
Associate Director&6&$\$50{,}000$\\\hline
Administrative Specialist&37&$\$23{,}000$\\\hline
\end{tabular}
solution: Since more than half the employees are Administrative Specialists, the median salary will be an administrative specialist, thus, $\boxed{\$23{,}000}$.
model_solution:
## Step 1: Determine the total number of employees
To find the median salary, we first need to determine the total number of employees. According to the table, the total number of employees is 1 (President) + 5 (Vice-President) + 10 (Director) + 6 (Associate Director) + 37 (Administrative Specialist) = 59.

## Step 2: Arrange the salaries in ascending order
We need to arrange the salaries in ascending order to find the median. The salaries in ascending order are: $\$23{,}000$ (37 times), $\$50{,}000$ (6 times), $\$75{,}000$ (10 times), $\$90{,}000$ (5 times), and $\$130{,}000$ (1 time).

## Step 3: Find the middle value
Since there are 59 employees (an odd number), the middle value is the 30th salary. This is because the median is the middle value in a dataset when it is ordered from smallest to largest. If we count the salaries from lowest to highest, the first 37 salaries are $\$23{,}000$, so the 30th salary will be within this group.

## Step 4: Determine the median salary
Since the 30th salary falls within the group of 37 Administrative Specialists who all have the same salary of $\$23{,}000$, the median salary is $\$23{,}000$.

The final answer is: $\boxed{23000}$
